c.OPFO-STRIPPABLE-COMMENT.g2:a.TEXT: 4/9/97 Ramesh Bug Fix: Defined a new symbolic-parameter opfom-default-priority-text-color (and a devu-scalar-initialization) to be used as the default text color for an out of range priority message. Earlier for an out of range priority message bith the text color and the background color were defaulting to opfom-default-priority-color thus making the message text invisible.

3/7/97 Ramesh Removed the two initially rules that were setting up the values of devu-low-priority and devu-medium-priority based on the array-length of opfom-priority-alarm-colors. These values set caused a status-error-display on the initialization UI, since the value provided by the highest init obj was different from the value provided by these rules. Anyway the user can set these using inits and also now smh is fixed so that if the message is sent with out of range priority it does not give error.

2/10/97 DVG Added common message headers. Commented out reference to smh-transient-message in _opfo-domain-object::opfom-priority-change, was producing error message but was not being used in the method.
11/18/96 Ramesh Fixed the procedure SMH-UPDATE-COLOR-SPOTS and used it as the devu-aux-procedure in the devu-vector intializations for smh-standard-background-colors and smh-standard-text-colors.
11/12/96 Ramesh Moved smh-private-color-configuration and smh-tc-color-configuration from smh in to opfom, since the alarm propagation depends on these color configurations. Now smh requires opfom.
11/12/96 Ramesh Moved the alarm propagation stuff, netu-user-propagation-methods, netu-propagation-methods, netu-alarm-propagation-initialization from dev_util in to the newly created opfom module.
2/15/96 Ramesh New Module for methods on opa-schematic-object. Currently has the alarm propagation methods.
